The algorithm presented in the paper has a time complexity that involves sorting and searching, which are typical operations in data structures. Hence, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves the partitioning of a polygon into cells, which is a problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.GR (Graph Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the time complexity of the algorithm, which is a problem in theoretical computer science. Hence, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a possible sub-category.
